article.headline: Portland St. 79, N. Colorado 66
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. (AP) -- Dupree Lucas scored a career-high 32 points to lead Portland State to a 79-66 win over Northern Colorado on Saturday night. Paul Hafford added 19 points off the bench for Portland State (11-6, 2-2 Big Sky). Lucas, who was 12-of-17 from the field, had averaged fewer than 10 points per game before Saturday. Portland State led 38-28 at halftime and kept the lead to double digits for much of the second half. The Bears (2-14, 0-4) were hurt by turnovers, including 11 in the first half that led to 14 Portland State points. The Vikings scored 21 points off 18 Northern Colorado turnovers for the game. Kirk Archibeque and Will Figures each scored 15 points for Northern Colorado.
